unittitle_ssm: de Caro, Mulvehill, and Menkhoff Family Papers
abstract_ssm: This collection contains a small selection of documents and photographs of three families of European immigrants who settled in New York City in the late 19th century. These families became connected through a series of marriages and their papers relate to a wide range of topics including marriage and courtship, the Italian-American community in New York City, Columbus Day, and travel accounts.
